This paper deals with the characterization of intracell interference and cluster inference for device-to-device (D2D) communication. It involves the use of stochastic processes and spatial statistics to model the topology of base stations and mobile terminals. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.MA), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
